Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 6
Total animals affected
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 2160/ 176/ 0/ 0/ 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors
Epidemiological comments: Before this event the disease was detected only in the south of Israel in 1989, 2006 and 2007. The herds are located in the north of the country, near the Syrian and Lebanese borders. All the cases are concentrated in the Golan Heights and the upper Galilee. Stomoxis flies and horn flies have been seen in the area.

Control measures
Measures applied: Control of arthropods; Quarantine: Movement control inside the country: Screening; Dipping/Spraying; Modified stamping out; No treatment of affected animals.

Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s);

Administrative division/ Species/ Total Vaccinated/ Details
Hazafon/ Cattle/ 44 136/ Sheep pox vaccine (Jovac)

Measures to be applied: No other measures

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since the start of the epizootic in early July 2012, 29 outbreaks have been reported to the OIE, all located along the Syrian and Lebanese borders in the Golan heights and Upper Galilee.

The interactive map at the source URL shows 5 outbreaks, 3 of which on the Golan heights, adjacent to the Syrian border, and 2 in the Upper Galilee, adjacent to Lebanon. No information on the lumpy skin disease situation in Lebanon and Syria has become available.

From the provided data it has not become clear how effective the vaccination is. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1z-1.]
